Hi Ralf

> is there anyone who happens to have an ADF of the WB3.0 HardDisk diskette?
> I've managed to find all my other disks, except this one, which in my memory was
> only delivered with the A1200HD package (1200 with harddisk built-in at
>  purchase time).

Yeah, that was annoying. You don't really need the disk though, as you can boot 
from the WB disk and copy everything onto the HD. If you need the HDToolBox 
(not sure if it was only ever on the Install disk) for partitioning the hard-
drive then you can get HDInstTools (I think) from Aminet, it does the same job.

If you need to format it, just do it from the WB.

Copy everything from the Workbench and Extras disk into the root of the HD. 
Copy the Storage, Locale and Fonts disks into subdirectories called Storage, 
Locale and Fonts.

From CLI (after booting from WB disk):

copy sys:#? dh0: all
copy extras3.0:#? dh0: all
copy storage3.0:#? dh0:Storage all
copy dh0:WBStartup.info dh0:Storage.info
